latestIgtvVideos.caption:
What’s light, breezy and perfect for staying cool this Sunday? Our summer specials! ☀️

Pair our Smoked Chicken And Broccoli Salad with a refreshing Cold Press Mango Juice. Order our range of summer drinks at any of our cafés or via Zomato or Swiggy!

We saved the best for last! Enjoy the summery flavours of our last seasonal coffee from the 2021 harvest! This deliciously fruity light roast comes from one of our most celebrated partner farms — Riverdale Estate. Interestingly, this coffee was fermented using a red fruit (somewhat like an apple) native to the Kodaikanal region. We’re loving the taste notes of plum, red grape and mandarin orange in this coffee! 🍑 🍇 🍊 

PS: This coffee tastes refreshingly peppy as a cold brew.
Happy Holi from our colourful family to yours!

Treat yourself to a warm cup of rich hot chocolate and a delicious buttery 🥐 this #HotChocolateDay.

What are you pairing your hot chocolate with today? 👇🏽

We’re offering FLAT 15% off on your favourite brands so you can hone your brewing skills from the comforts of your home and get the best out of your coffee beans. Click the link in our bio to get your hands on some of our premium gear! 🏠 ☕️

latestIgtvVideos.title: Behind the Beans EP 1 | Kerehaklu Estate
latestIgtvVideos.caption: Welcome to our all-new IGTV series! Our first episode kicked off on November 23, 2021 with a live interactive session with our roasters @chitnis13 and @t.j.r___, along with @thipaiah from Kerehaklu Estate. Our roasters in conversation with Pranoy discussed all things coffee — including our first-ever Robusta in collaboration with @kerehaklu, untimely rains and how they affect the harvest, and a whole lot more. Sit back, have your favourite brew ready and watch the video to know what goes on behind the scenes of making some of India's best coffee! ☕ 🌱

latestIgtvVideos.title: Coffee's Next Generation
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
This #InternationalCoffeeDay, we're celebrating change. As the younger generation takes over, we are already seeing so many new and exciting changes taking place in the coffee industry in India. At Blue Tokai, we're proud to have partnered with farms who support the next generation of young men and women in coffee and bring their innovative ideas to life. We also encourage our teams to bring changes that benefit the coffee community and build a brighter future. 

Here's to the younger generation of growers, roasters, baristas and everyone in the coffee community bringing some of the country's best coffee to palates across the world. 💙

latestPosts.caption:
Producer Series ’25 opens with a welcome return from Prakashan Balaraman of Riverdale Estate, a pioneer pushing Indian coffee forward through experiments with fruit fermentation and rare varietals.

For this lot, Prakashan went a step further. Having mastered single fruit fermentation, he pushed boundaries by using a blend of tropical fruits during fermentation instead of just one. The result? A cup with bright acidity, a welcome lack of funk, and clean fruit notes. 

So, if you’re someone who enjoys a delightfully complex brew with fruity layers, you’d want to invite this one home. 

Order this limited-edition coffee by clicking the link in our bio.

#ProducerSeries #BTCoffeeLaunch

latestPosts.caption:
This weekend, we hosted a special evening at Blue Tokai Origins. 💙

The first of many, this gathering brought together some truly wonderful minds, each shaping the future of business in India. It was a joy to have the space come alive with laughter, conversations, and ideas, all shared over special brews and meals curated for the occasion. 

Thank you to everyone who joined us and made the evening memorable. We can’t wait to host you again!

#BlueTokaiOrigins

At Origins, Jitendra and Sanjeev from @suchalisartisanbakehouse helm our live bakery. 

Each day, the duo perfects a range of bakes, from fresh sourdough loaves and milk breads to twice-baked croissants, cookies and more. They move with ease that only years spent honing your craft brings, and a taste of their expertise carries through in everything that comes out of our ovens. 

The breads they bake ground so many meals in our menu, and are available fresh off the rack for you to take home. Drop by to pick a loaf today. 💙

#BlueTokaiOrigins #SuchalisArtisanBakehouse

This month at the Blue Tokai Book Club, we’re reading Sakina’s Kiss by Vivek Shanbhag — a novel that doesn’t shout, but leaves you unsettled in the quietest, most precise ways.

The story begins with a knock at the door — two strangers claiming to know Venkat’s daughter. What follows is not just a tense domestic moment, but a slow unraveling of memory, class, morality, and control. Shanbhag doesn’t rush. He invites you to sit with discomfort, to notice the silences, to question what lies beneath the surface of an “ordinary” life.

Set in Bangalore, but strikingly universal in its themes, Sakina’s Kiss is the kind of novel that stays with you—not for what it says, but for what it leaves unsaid.

Book courtesy @bahrisons_booksellers 

#BlueTokaiBookClub #BTBookClub

latestPosts.caption:
Ever wondered how technique shapes flavour? 

Come by Blue Tokai Origins and let curiosity take over. At our Play Bar, we bring together the most manual brewing methods we’ve ever featured in a cafe. Here, you get to observe and taste how each brings out something distinct in your cup. 

From the Chemex that crafts a clean, complex brew highlighting delicate flavour notes to the Syphon that brews a full-bodied cup with a smooth mouthfeel, seven unique ways to enjoy your coffee await. 

Our baristas, Shivani, Sourav, Aman, and Ajit would love to help you discover all our manual brewing station has to offer. 

#BlueTokaiOrigins

Coffee from some of our favourite Indian estates travels all the way to Japan, where Ryota roasts them with precision at our Yaita Roastery. He spent time in India working closely with Subham, our head roaster in India, learning our roasting style and the unique character of our single origin beans. 

The result? Roasts crafted for Japan’s palate and love for Pour Overs, while being rooted in our signature style. The selection includes both bold, dark blends like Sumire and Cauvery Peak, and delicate, aromatic light roasts like Riverdale N72 and Howdia Estate, our most loved in Japan last season. 

Slide 2: Ryota from our Japan team with Jahangir, Subham and Durgesh, our roasters in India.

#BlueTokaiJapan

A few days back, we held the Pune edition of our Cup Tasters Championship, a sensory challenge that rewards speed and precision. With a farm tour for two to win, it brought together some of the sharpest palates from our community.

The energy was infectious. The competition was fierce. But what we loved most was a palpable sense of community that coloured the evening.

Congratulations to all the winners, and thanks to all the participants, and our partners @sangameshwar_coffee and @benkibrewingtools for making it so much fun!

Where should we host the next Cup Tasters Championship? Drop your city in the comments below 👇

#CupTastersChampionship

latestPosts.caption:
Sunday breakfast, sorted! 🥑☀️

Our guacamole on toast is creamy, hearty, and just the right kind of messy.

Pair it with a favourite brew and call it a morning well spent.

They say that when something is made with love, you can taste it. And at Blue Tokai Origins, love and craft shape our meals in equal measure. 

The care with which Chef Auroni and Suchali designed our menu is carried forward by Chef Mukesh and the team on the ground, who make sure every plate is just right. From the open toasts, club sandwiches, and brioche bun burgers that feature artisanal breads to the desserts that add a sweet finish to every meal, each dish carries an imprint of @suchalisartisanbakehouse’s craft. 

It’s the small things, done well, that make this place feel like more than just a café. 

#BlueTokaiOrigins

latestPosts.caption:
Want a smooth, refreshing batch of cold brew for the day? All it takes is a good night’s steep.

Get brewing with our Cold Brew Bags, available at our cafés, on our website, and through Swiggy and Zomato.

#SummerWithBT

We’ve created Origins, a space for you to slow down and: 

• Experience some of our rarest coffees, preserved at peak flavour in a temperature-controlled environment we call The Coffee Cellar. 

• Take home a loaf of artisanal bread baked fresh in front of you by @suchalisartisanbakehouse. 

• Savour a carefully curated menu that elicits comfort and reflects craft. 

• Discover unique facets of your favourite beans, brewed using more methods than we’ve ever featured at any of our cafes. 

It’s a living, breathing space, with even more to come. We can’t wait to welcome you there! 💙

#BlueTokaiOrigins

Just like the coffee producers we work with, our dairy partners are carefully chosen. From Whyte Farms in Delhi NCR to Akshayakalpa in Bangalore and Sarda Farms in Nashik, our dairy partners focus on delivering fresh, natural milk that’s free from additives and hormones. 

They ensure clean, healthy feed for their cows, maintain transparent processes you can trust, and keep the milk fresh by minimizing the time between milking and delivery—all while handling the milk carefully from farm to cup.

For those who prefer non-dairy alternatives, we offer oat, soy, and almond milk at all our cafés.

This World Milk Day, we honour them for making possible the espresso-based brews we love to drink and share. 

#WorldMilkDay
